comments.body:
Looking at this a bit more, would an API roughly like the following work?
{code:cpp}
struct IpcPayloadSequence; // Internally std::vector<std::shared_ptr<IpcPayload>>
Result<std::shared_ptr<IpcPayloadSequence>> RecordBatchToPayload(const RecordBatch&);
Result<std::shared_ptr<IpcPayloadSequence>> SchemaToPayload(const Schema&);
int64_t GetPayloadSize(const IpcPayloadSequence&);

class RecordBatchWriter {
  Status WritePayloads(const IpcPayloadSequence&);
};
{code}
This avoids exposing IpcPayload directly. (There probably needs to be more state to help RecordBatchWriter know whether the payload is a schema, has all the necessary dictionary batches, etc.)

(For context, this would be useful to help limit the on-network message sizes in Flight, to avoid tripping limits in gRPC and help manage memory usage by Netty/gRPC.)
